According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Water Mist Fire Fighting System Market was valued at USD 314 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 334 million in 2025 to USD 481 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth as industries, commercial buildings, transportation infrastructure, and critical facilities increasingly adopt advanced fire suppression systems that deliver superior protection while significantly reducing water consumption and minimizing asset damage. Rising emphasis on sustainable building practices, stringent fire safety regulations, and growing investments in smart infrastructure continue to strengthen market demand across Europe.
